generated.description: This is an autogenerated partial class definition of 'ChemicalConsumptionPerMass'

description*.en: In the context of a chemical durability test, this is measure of how much of a solution (often a corrosive or reactive one) is consumed or used up per unit mass of a material being tested. In other words, this the volume of solution needed to cause a certain level of chemical reaction or damage to a given mass of the material.
